  - @ssi-anik There may be problems if the function name starts with a dash, but otherwise a dash is fine. Conventionally the file name is the function name and the function name is an underscore followed by the command name. This works fine even for command names that contain a dash, e.g. `_pkg-config` and `_invoke-rc.d`.
  
  
  
